`template/` is the scaffold root distributed into every new project via `update-template.sh`: it carries the `.context/` tree's git-merge policy plus the full CI/lint/generator toolchain under `scripts/`.

The only cross-cutting invariant at this level is naming consistency between `.gitattributes`'s glob patterns and however `.context/` file layout (`.ctx`, `rollup.ctx`) is produced elsewhere — if that layout convention changes, the merge-driver patterns here must change with it. `.gitattributes` currently declares a `ctx-regenerate` merge driver that has no backing implementation yet, so any real merge conflict on `.ctx` files must be resolved manually (`ctx-resummarize <path>`) until that driver exists.

`scripts/` is self-contained: it owns the check-script/generator contract (shared file-enumeration convention, `FAIL:` diagnostic shape, marker-splice conventions) internally, and nothing in `template/`'s top level depends on or duplicates that contract — this rollup only needs to know that `scripts/` is where all invocable tooling lives and that `update-template.sh` is the sync entrypoint pulling both `.gitattributes`-style config and the scripts themselves from upstream.

No intent.md exists for this directory, so no divergence check is possible.